First antenna three-jointed, second article shortest, and distal article bearing a number (six?) of aesthetascs, with no gap or difference between apical and subapical aesthetascs. Second antenna (
Fig. 4
) short and stout, if bent backwards hardly reaching posterior margin of first tergite. Two-jointed flagellum bearing apical cone of about half the length of the apical article; lateral setae approximately 0.25 times as long as apical cone, and inserted at its basal 0.2. Articles of second antenna with narrow setae and overlapping cuticular scales.
